</taxonomicName>
and was up to date considered endemic of 
<collectingCountry id="63E56DAAF54B1876FEB5C95F3BAEFD8E" box="[371,438,569,591]" name="Jordan" pageId="3" pageNumber="1508">Jordan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="7F6350CBF54B1876FE01C95F38FAFD8E" author="NIKODYM M" box="[455,738,567,591]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1508" pagination="87 - 97" refId="ref18162" refString="NIKODYM M. &amp; A. BEZDEK (2016): Glaphyridae, pp. 87 - 97. - In: LOBL I. E. &amp; D. LOBL (eds), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Volume 3, Scarabaeoidea, Scirtoidea, Dascilloidea, Buprestoidea, Byrrhoidea. Revised and updated edition. Brill; Leiden, Boston. XXVIII + 983 pp." type="book chapter" year="2016">NIKODÝM &amp; BEZDĚK 2016</bibRefCitation>
). A paper addressing taxonomy and distribution of this pair of species is in preparation.
</paragraph>
